column31: "Inzko's law would not have been passed if it had not been done by the SDA. I will tell you a secret. The SDA organized letters from the Mothers of Srebrenica and the camp inmates. We wrote them and sent them to fifteen hundred addresses: kings, presidents, prime ministers, parliamentarians, senators in the European Union, in the countries of the European Union, in America, all signed by camp inmates and Mothers of Srebrenica. And when you send them to fifteen hundred significant addresses, 10 percent of those people react, so you get 150 lobbyists who say this is really not right. Imagine they even gave Karadžić a decoration! So we pressured Inzko to do what he did, he avoided us for awhile, in the end he didn't even answer my calls. But he realized that he would leave Bosnia and Hercegovina in defeat, so then the day he decided to sign, he went to Potočare among the gravestones and signed it there. A day before it was announced. Even today they talk, make a lot of noise, deny, but almost nobody denies the genocide anymore. On that they're silent. So you can persuade people. And we have to fight, regardless of all the risks and reactions. HDZ, we have to live with the Croats, but they will not get the things they are trying to help them get. They won't get the exclusivity to block us further. They will get fair resolutions. What they deserve to get. How to get the power, how to get military power, and do we have a response to, God forbid, the worst case scenario? We do. We have calculated our numbers.. How many hunters we have, how many young people, how many drone instructors and so on, I won't go into detail. But just so you know. Part of our strength is in the diaspora, because at least a quarter of people in their prime, family people with children, educated people, have left Bosnia and Herzegovina, at least a quarter, and they must not be left behind, forgotten. So we have to activate that strength, I have been spending a lot of time in the diaspora, a month during the last six months, sleeping in hotels in Germany, Scandinavia, and Ramić and others for more than three months. In the beginning it seemed that they didn't react, they were complaining a lot, and then they started to, you know, before they turned on the ignition and couldn't even start the motor, but we did, and now we got 92,000 people registered in very complex procedures. So, this time, there could be a slight upheaval in the elections, thanks to the diaspora. Bosniaks and Bosnians are in agreement, we are being insulted, but we will defeat them and only then will we invite them join us again. Inflation, price increases, printing the euro and the dollar the way the dinar used to be printed at Topčider. And every time they print, they steal a few billion and a few tens of millions from our Bosnian pockets. There is no way to stop the price increase, it's global, it's like a rising tide, you can't stop the tide, but you can build a boat so that the people don't drown. So increase wages, and we're constantly working on that. The first round will include 800 thousand people who are having a hard time, half of them pensioners. And then the second round will begin the day after tomorrow with the budget and all the risks that it entails, the federal one. To help people who are having a hard time. Economy, construction, roads, energy, food, people need to work on that. And the young people who leave will have to be compensated to a large extent with HAJ TEH technologies and robotics. And the armed forces will therefore have to be supplemented by robots, first of all drones, or rather, flying robots. Corruption, it eats at the root. Alija once told a story about how his mother loved flowers and ten flowers were growing beautifully, the eleventh one was drying up, so she called him and pulled the flower out of the pot, there were worms down there, they were eating the root. And so the flower dried up, the tree dried up. This is what corruption does, it is everywhere. Wherever a person puts his personal interests before national interests we have that problem, there is a lot of that, and we need to fight it. At this time, what we see is that the SDA has opposed the three lobbies, did not agree with them so that they could promote their campaign. So, one is a bookmaker lobby, the other is a lobby that wanted three hundred small power plants to cut off three hundred rivers and streams, so we stopped it, and in spite of all the risks, angered that lobby, pushed it towards others, and finally, in Sarajevo they wanted to build huge buildings on Skenderija, and we stopped that. We made enemies of these people. But we will preserve the clean air in Sarajevo, we will preserve those rivers, we will tax those bookmakers who earn an incredible three and a half billion a year without paying taxes. column31: Kako javljaju ruski mediji, na glasanjima će biti regionalnih razlika. U Donjecku i Lugansku na papiru će biti samo jedno pitanje: „da“ ili „ne“ za priključenje Ruskoj Federaciji. U Hersonu i Zaporožju se postavljaju tri pitanja, na koja treba da se odgovori sa jednim „da“ ili „ne“: izlazak iz Ukrajine, osnivanje nezavisne države i priključenje Rusiji. Glasaće se i u Rusiji, gdje je od 2014. godine izbjeglo stotine hiljada Ukrajinaca. Međutim, velika većina, nekoliko miliona, pobjegla je u oblasti Ukrajine koji su pod kontrolom Kijeva.
